ae423.textContent: Mechanism of action of caffeine on:

cfc5a.textContent:
Caffeine boosts muscle contraction 
by increasing calcium release 
from the sarcoplasmic reticulum.

publicationXrefe63.standardName: Caffeine and Clinical Outcomes in Premature Neonates.

comments.content: Caffeine promotes intracellular calcium release by activating ryanodine receptors on the sarcoplasmic reticulum of skeletal and smooth muscle, enhancing muscle contraction.  Inspired by [Figure 1 in Kumar and Lipshultz, 2019](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC6915633).
